msgid_plural "Rebel's Suppressors"
msgstr[0] "反抗者消音器"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"This modified suppressor allows for gas to escape, while reducing sound to a"
" minimal. You don't know but the suppressor might be magic. After all, who "
"could have made this with only a toolbox and good-will?"
msgstr "这款改装消音器允许气体逸出，同时将声音降至最低。你或许不知道，但这消音器可能带有魔力。毕竟，谁能仅凭一个工具箱和善意就造出这东西？"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "muzzle"
msgstr "枪口"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "EOTech EXPS3-4 Holographic Hybrid Sight"
msgid_plural "EOTech EXPS3-4 Holographic Hybrid Sights"
msgstr[0] "EOTech EXPS3-4全息混合瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A hybrid sight meant for long range and short range engagements."
msgstr "一款适用于远距离和近距离交战的混合瞄准镜。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "sights"
msgstr "瞄准具"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "EOTech EXP-729 SSS"
msgid_plural "EOTech EXP-729 SSSs"
msgstr[0] "EOTech EXP-729 SSS"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"The EXP-729 SSS is a short sighted scope meant for small close range "
"engagements."
msgstr "EXP-729 SSS是一款短视距瞄准镜，专为小型近距离交战设计。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Trijicon Iluminator Sight"
msgid_plural "Trijicon Iluminator Sights"
msgstr[0] "Trijicon照明瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"The Iluminator is close range/barrel to barrel fights meant for SMGs and "
"shotguns."
msgstr "照明瞄准镜适用于近距离/枪口对枪口的战斗，专为冲锋枪和霰弹枪设计。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Trijicon 1x24 Sight"
msgid_plural "Trijicon 1x24 Sights"
msgstr[0] "Trijicon 1x24瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A medium range reflex sight that allows for quick target changes."
msgstr "一款中距离反射式瞄准镜，可实现快速目标切换。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Sightmark Mini-Shot Reflex Sight"
msgid_plural "Sightmark Mini-Shot Reflex Sights"
msgstr[0] "Sightmark Mini-Shot反射式瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A super small sight that will really only fit on small weapons."
msgstr "一款超小型瞄准镜，仅适用于小型武器。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Trijicon 1x42 Sight"
msgid_plural "Trijicon 1x42 Sights"
msgstr[0] "Trijicon 1x42瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A long range reflex sight that allows for quick target changes."
msgstr "一款远距离反射式瞄准镜，可实现快速目标切换。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Ultra Duel Shot Pro Night Vision Sight."
msgid_plural "Ultra Duel Shot Pro Night Vision Sight.s"
msgstr[0] "Ultra Duel Shot Pro夜视瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"A short range glowing sight that allows for increased viability at night."
msgstr "一款短距离发光瞄准镜，可提升夜间作战的可见性。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Laser Duel Shot Reflex Sight"
msgid_plural "Laser Duel Shot Reflex Sights"
msgstr[0] "Laser Duel Shot反射式瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A reflex sight that has a built-in laser sight."
msgstr "一款内置激光瞄准器的反射式瞄准镜。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "ACOG 4x32mm Rifle Scope"
msgid_plural "ACOG 4x32mm Rifle Scopes"
msgstr[0] "ACOG 4x32mm 步枪瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A long/medium scope used by everything... Well, nearly."
msgstr "一款适用于几乎所有武器的中/长程瞄准镜……嗯，差不多是全部。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "VX-3 Rifle Scope"
msgid_plural "VX-3 Rifle Scopes"
msgstr[0] "VX-3 步枪瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A long range scope used by hunting rifles."
msgstr "一款用于猎枪的远程瞄准镜。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Spectre DR Duel Role Sights"
msgid_plural "Spectre DR Duel Role Sightss"
msgstr[0] "Spectre DR 双用途瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A cool as hell ACOG-like sight used by NATO countries."
msgstr "一款北约国家使用的酷似ACOG的瞄准镜，帅到没边。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "P-223 Rifle Scope"
msgid_plural "P-223 Rifle Scopes"
msgstr[0] "P-223 步枪瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A short range scope used by hunting rifles."
msgstr "一款用于猎枪的短程瞄准镜。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "V-XR Patrol Rifle Scope"
msgid_plural "V-XR Patrol Rifle Scopes"
msgstr[0] "V-XR 巡逻步枪瞄准镜"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A medium range scope used by hunting rifles."
msgstr "一款用于猎枪的中程瞄准镜。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ".460 Rowland caliber conversion kit"
msgid_plural ".460 Rowland caliber conversion kits"
msgstr[0] ".460 Rowland 口径转换套件"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"A conversion kit for the M1911 pistol to allow it the ability to fire the "
".460 Rowland pistol caliber. Don't forget the muzzle break!"
msgstr "用于M1911手枪的转换套件，使其能够发射.460 Rowland手枪弹。别忘了装上枪口制退器！"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "bore"
msgstr "枪管"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ".460 Rowland muzzle brake"
msgid_plural ".460 Rowland muzzle brakes"
msgstr[0] ".460 Rowland 枪口制退器"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"A muzzle break meant specifically for the M1911 conversion. Found in all "
".460 Rowland conversion kits at your local Artyoms' Gun Emporium."
msgstr "专为M1911转换套件设计的枪口制退器。在您当地的阿尔乔姆枪械店里，所有.460 Rowland转换套件中都能找到它。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Artyom's Custom .460 Rowland Conversion Kit"
msgid_plural "Artyom's Custom .460 Rowland Conversion Kits"
msgstr[0] "阿尔乔姆定制 .460 Rowland 转换套件"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Artyom's Custom .460 Rowland Conversion Kit",
#. 'str_pl': "Artyom's Custom .460 Rowland Conversion Kits"}
#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"A conversion kit for the M1911 to make it shoot .460 Rowland. Dissemble it "
"to get the stuff you need!"
msgstr "用于M1911手枪的转换套件，使其能够发射.460 Rowland弹。拆解它来获取你需要的部件！"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "GP-25"
msgid_plural "GP-25"
msgstr[0] "GP-25"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"A Russian grenade launcher compatible with Warsaw pact weapons. But this one"
" is a recreation of the GP-25 that fits Warsaw AND NATO weapons. And fires "
"the 40mm used by the M203."
msgstr "一款兼容华约武器的俄罗斯榴弹发射器。但这个是GP-25的复刻版，适用于华约和北约武器，并能发射M203使用的40mm榴弹。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "rail"
msgstr "导轨"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "GP-30"
msgid_plural "GP-30"
msgstr[0] "GP-30"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"A Russian grenade launcher compatible with Warsaw pact weapons. But this one"
" is a recreation of the GP-30 that fits Warsaw AND NATO weapons. And fires "
"the 40mm used by the M203. A more accurate version of the GP-25"
msgstr ""
"一款兼容华约武器的俄罗斯榴弹发射器。但这个是GP-30的复刻版，适用于华约和北约武器，并能发射M203使用的40mm榴弹。这是GP-25的更精准版本。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "BG-15"
msgid_plural "BG-15"
msgstr[0] "BG-15"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"A Russian grenade launcher compatible with Warsaw pact weapons. But this one"
" is a recreation of the BG-15 that fits Warsaw AND NATO weapons. And fires "
"the 40mm used by the M203. The first of the Russian launchers."
msgstr ""
"一款兼容华约武器的俄罗斯榴弹发射器。但这个是BG-15的复刻版，适用于华约和北约武器，并能发射M203使用的40mm榴弹。这是俄罗斯榴弹发射器中的第一款。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "space gun shot"
msgid_plural "space gun shots"
msgstr[0] "太空枪弹药"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "A modification meant for the space gun."
msgstr "专为太空枪设计的改装部件。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "underbarrel"
msgstr "下挂式"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Grunt's Big Boys"
msgid_plural "Grunt's Big Boys"
msgstr[0] "大兵的重火力"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"This peculiar set-up of two M203 launchers duck-taped to the sides of the "
"Grunt makes it look ridiculous. But in practice, the soldier who made this "
"becomes a one-man mortar team. Slinging massive explosive rounds down range "
"onto unsuspecting zombies and whatnot. A genius of a modification"
msgstr ""
"这套奇特的装置将两个M203发射器用胶带绑在“大兵”两侧，看起来十分滑稽。但实际上，制作它的士兵变成了单人迫击炮小队，能将巨大的爆炸性弹药射向远处的毫无防备的僵尸等等。这是一个天才般的改装。"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "Pedersen Device Kit"
msgid_plural "Pedersen Device Kits"
msgstr[0] "佩德森装置套件"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"Replacing several key parts of a .30-06, 7.62x51mm, 7.62x54R, .303, or "
"7.62x39mm  firearm converting it into a shorter range, semi-automatic "
"carbine. Much more accurate and controllable than the original rifle, it was"
" supposed to be the Wonder Weapon of WWI for the Allies... in 1919. The "
"originals are incredibly rare, however this reproduction includes the kit, "
"chambered in .32 ACP and ready for use in seconds with all major WWI "
"weapons. Score!"
msgstr ""
"通过替换.30-06、7.62x51mm、7.62x54R、.303或7.62x39mm枪械的若干关键部件，将其改造为射程较短、半自动的卡宾枪。比原版步枪更精准且易于操控，本应成为1919年协约国在一战中的“奇迹武器”……原版极为罕见，但这套复刻套件包含改装组件，可适配.32"
" ACP口径，并能与所有主要一战武器快速装配使用。太棒了！"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid "8mm Mauser caliber conversion kit"
msgid_plural "8mm Mauser caliber conversion kits"
msgstr[0] "8毫米毛瑟口径转换套件"

#: .\art_mods.json
msgid ""
"This kit is used to convert a shotgun or 7.62x39mm, .303, 7.62x54R, "
"7.62x51mm, or .30-06 rifle to the famous and powerful 7.62x51mm caliber.  "
"The conversion results in reduced ammo capacity and a slight reduction to "
"accuracy."
msgstr ""
"此套件用于将霰弹枪或7.62x39mm、.303、7.62x54R、7.62x51mm、.30-06步枪转换为著名且威力强大的7.92x57mm毛瑟口径。改装后会降低弹药容量并轻微影响精度。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Browning Hi-Power"
msgid_plural "Browning Hi-Power"
msgstr[0] "勃朗宁大威力手枪"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A old but still relatively powerful and reliable semi-auto pistol from "
"Belgium. Rechambered to fire the ever so powerful 10mm round."
msgstr "一款来自比利时的老式半自动手枪，仍具备相当的威力和可靠性。经过改膛后可发射威力强大的10毫米子弹。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Remington R51-Subcompact"
msgid_plural "Remington R51-Subcompact"
msgstr[0] "雷明顿R51袖珍型"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A subcompact pistol made by Remington. Features a extremely light build and "
"easy trigger pull. The perfect drop weapon."
msgstr "雷明顿制造的袖珍手枪。采用极轻量化设计，扳机力度轻柔。完美的备用武器。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Rebel"
msgid_plural "Rebel"
msgstr[0] "反抗者"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A modified Browning HP pistol showing a lot of wear-n-tear. But don't let "
"that fool you, the weapon is accurate, powerful, and near silent thanks to "
"it's unique sound suppressor. The weapon has the phrase Fight the Power! "
"scratched in by a knife on the right side of the slide. It was most likely "
"made during the first few riots in the beginning of the Cataclysm."
msgstr ""
"一把经过改装、布满磨损痕迹的勃朗宁HP手枪。但别被外表欺骗——得益于独特的消音器，这把武器精准、威力强大且近乎无声。套筒右侧有用刀刻下的“反抗强权！”字样。很可能制作于大灾变初期的骚乱期间。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Beretta Px4 Storm Subcompact"
msgid_plural "Beretta Px4 Storm Subcompact"
msgstr[0] "伯莱塔Px4风暴袖珍型"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A small, compact pistol made by Beretta. Light and agile, its use is more "
"than just a pistol; it's a life saver."
msgstr "伯莱塔制造的小型紧凑手枪。轻巧灵活，它不仅是手枪，更是救命利器。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "SIG P224"
msgid_plural "SIG P224"
msgstr[0] "西格P224"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A very small, pocket pistol made by Sig Sauer for when you need to put a gun"
" in your back pocket just in case. The perfect weapon to put it on the "
"temple of a zombie and blow it's brains all over the wall. Great fun!"
msgstr "西格绍尔制造的微型口袋手枪，专为随身隐蔽携带而设计。最适合抵近丧尸太阳穴开火，让脑浆溅满墙壁。乐趣十足！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "SIG P220"
msgid_plural "SIG P220"
msgstr[0] "西格P220"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The first pistol made by Sig Sauer, quoted to be the most accurate pistol "
"right out of the box. Well it does say that, and it sure does show."
msgstr "西格绍尔制造的首款手枪，被誉为开箱即用的最精准手枪。宣传所言非虚，实际表现也确实如此。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "SIG P227"
msgid_plural "SIG P227"
msgstr[0] "西格P227"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A slim, .45 ACP pistol made by SIG. Exceptional and robust, the P227 might "
"just be the perfect .45"
msgstr "西格制造的.45 ACP薄型手枪。性能卓越、结构坚固，P227或许就是完美的.45口径手枪。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "SIG P220 Scorpion"
msgid_plural "SIG P220 Scorpion"
msgstr[0] "西格P220蝎式"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A special edition of the SIG P220, custom grips, custom finish, custom "
"everything. All in a nice desert paint job. Even comes with a threaded "
"barrel!"
msgstr "西格P220特别版，配备定制握把、表面处理及全套改装。采用漂亮的沙漠涂装，甚至附带螺纹枪管！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "SIG P226"
msgid_plural "SIG P226"
msgstr[0] "西格P226"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A modern semi-automatic handgun that fires 9x19mm. It's used by police "
"forces all around the world. Though it didn't help them when the cataclysm "
"struck... But hey, they were probably all stupid. You're not stupid, are "
"you?"
msgstr ""
"发射9x19mm子弹的现代半自动手枪，被全球警队广泛采用。虽然大灾变降临时这并没帮上他们什么忙……不过嘛，那些警察大概都很蠢。你可不蠢，对吧？"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "FN FNP-9"
msgid_plural "FN FNP-9"
msgstr[0] "FN FNP-9"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A modern semi-automatic handgun that fires 9x19mm. Made by the guys who "
"created the FN Five-Seven. This underestimated little pistol packs one hell "
"of a punch. This being from Belgium; I'm not surprised it's good in a bar "
"fight."
msgstr ""
"发射9x19mm子弹的现代半自动手枪，由制造FN Five-"
"Seven的团队打造。这款被低估的小手枪威力惊人。既然产自比利时，它在酒吧斗殴中表现出色我倒毫不意外。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "FN FNX-9"
msgid_plural "FN FNX-9"
msgstr[0] "FN FNX-9"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A modern semi-automatic handgun that fires 9x19mm. Made by the guys who "
"created the FN Five-Seven. This underestimated little pistol packs one hell "
"of a punch. This being from Belgium; I'm not surprised it's good in a bar "
"fight. And this one has an X in the title so you just know it's supper edgy!"
msgstr ""
"发射9x19mm子弹的现代半自动手枪，由制造FN Five-"
"Seven的团队打造。这款被低估的小手枪威力惊人。既然产自比利时，它在酒吧斗殴中表现出色我倒毫不意外。而且名称里带个X，你就知道它超级前卫！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Swiss P210"
msgid_plural "Swiss P210"
msgstr[0] "瑞士P210"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A old, but very reliable side arm made by the soon-to-be SIG. Robust, "
"accurate, and extremely rare. This pistol sure got some fire to it. "
"Hopefully these zombies don't put out that fire huh?"
msgstr "由后来演变为西格的公司制造的旧式但非常可靠的随身武器。坚固、精准且极为稀有。这把枪确实火力十足。但愿丧尸们不会浇灭这股火焰，嗯？"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M1911A1"
msgid_plural "M1911A1"
msgstr[0] "M1911A1"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The M1911A1 was the updated version of the 1911 from 1924. This is the "
"version of the pistol that ran through WWII to Desert Storm, and is still in"
" use today."
msgstr "M1911A1是1911手枪于1924年推出的升级版。这款手枪从二战服役至沙漠风暴行动，至今仍在被使用。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Shanxi Type 17"
msgid_plural "Shanxi Type 17"
msgstr[0] "山西17式"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A .45 ACP version of the Mauser C96 produced in China. Features a short "
"action and plenty of firepower. You should know this gun from Metal Gear "
"Solid 3. If you don't... What is wrong with you?!"
msgstr "中国生产的毛瑟C96 .45 ACP版本。采用短行程枪机，火力强劲。你应该从《合金装备3》中认识这把枪。如果不认识……那你有什么毛病？！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "semi auto"
msgstr "半自动"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "burst"
msgstr "连发"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M1916 Prussian Red 9"
msgid_plural "M19116 Prussian Red 9"
msgstr[0] "M1916普鲁士红9"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The 9mm variant of the Mauser C96. Over 150,000 were made to outpace the "
"Luger. A large number 9 is burned into the broomhandle in red, a distinct "
"look. "
msgstr "毛瑟C96的9毫米变体。为超越鲁格手枪而生产了超过15万支。枪柄上烙有醒目的红色数字9，外观独特。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Luger PO8"
msgid_plural "Luger PO8"
msgstr[0] "鲁格PO8"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Luger PO8 is a semi-automatic 9mm shooting handgun used by the German "
"Empire and by Nazis around the globe. Actually, this one is in .45..."
msgstr "鲁格PO8是一款半自动9毫米手枪，曾被德意志帝国及全球纳粹使用。实际上，这把是.45口径的……"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "CZ 52"
msgid_plural "CZ 52"
msgstr[0] "CZ 52"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Czechoslovakian military pistol in 1952 gained great popularity when it "
"first rolled off the production line. Supporting great accuracy and bullet "
"penetration thanks to the 7.62x25 round that it was chambered in. Not the "
"most reliable though."
msgstr ""
"这款1952年的捷克斯洛伐克军用 pistol 在首次下线时广受欢迎。得益于其使用的7.62x25毫米弹药，具有出色的精度和穿甲能力，但可靠性并非最佳。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "CZ 75"
msgid_plural "CZ 75"
msgstr[0] "CZ 75"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A Czechoslovakian semi-auto military pistol introduced in 1975 and became "
"one of the original 'wonder nines', fairly accurate and with a common ammo "
"type. Makes this weapon a good addition to any gun nut's arsenal."
msgstr ""
"一款1975年推出的捷克斯洛伐克半自动军用 "
"pistol，成为最初的“奇迹九毫米”之一，精度不错且使用常见弹药类型。这把武器是任何枪械爱好者的军火库中的绝佳补充。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "IWI Jericho 941"
msgid_plural "IWI Jericho 941"
msgstr[0] "IWI杰里科941"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A Israeli defence weapon marketed in the US and parts of the UK as the Baby "
"Eagle. It's not a desert eagle by any means. But kinda looks like it."
msgstr "一款以色列防御武器，在美国和英国部分地区以“小鹰”之名销售。它绝非沙漠之鹰，但看起来有点像。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Automag"
msgid_plural "Automag"
msgstr[0] "自动马格南"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A not-so-beloved .44 caliber semi-auto pistol. Known for it breaking and "
"exploding in the users hand instead of being an actual gun. Still packs a "
"punch though... When it works."
msgstr "一款不太受欢迎的.44口径半自动手枪。以在用户手中断裂或爆炸而非正常运作而闻名。不过威力依然强劲……当它能用的时候。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "CZ 83"
msgid_plural "CZ 83"
msgstr[0] "CZ 83"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A Czechoslovakian semi-auto civilian pistol introduced in 1983 to replace "
"the CZ 52. Very accurate and reliable thanks to its chrome plated barrel and"
" well built frame."
msgstr "一款1983年推出的捷克斯洛伐克半自动民用 pistol，旨在取代CZ 52。得益于镀铬枪管和坚固的枪身，精度和可靠性极高。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Fort 12"
msgid_plural "Fort 12"
msgstr[0] "Fort 12"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A Ukrainian designed and produced pistol firing the ever so popular 9x18mm "
"round. Small for its use as a police pistol, the Fort 12 boasts great "
"Ukrainian reliability and good accuracy for stalken your STALKER."
msgstr ""
"一款乌克兰设计生产的手枪，发射广受欢迎的9x18毫米弹药。作为警用手枪尺寸小巧，Fort 12以其可靠的乌克兰品质和良好的精度，适合潜行你的《潜行者》。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Glock 34"
msgid_plural "Glock 34"
msgstr[0] "格洛克34"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"Competition version of the Glock 19. Much more accurate and slightly lighter"
" thinks to its weird muzzle drifting system to negate muzzle rise while also"
" decreasing weight in the front end of the gun. An amazing pistol; but sadly"
" not many upgrades available."
msgstr "格洛克19的竞赛版本。得益于其奇特的枪口漂移系统，抵消枪口上跳的同时减轻了前端重量，精度更高且略轻。一把出色的手枪；但可惜可用的升级不多。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Glock 18"
msgid_plural "Glock 18"
msgstr[0] "格洛克18"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A fully automatic variant of the Glock 17. The Glock 18 features are exactly"
" the same compared to the Glock 17."
msgstr "格洛克17的全自动变体。格洛克18的特性与格洛克17完全相同。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "auto"
msgstr "自动"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Glock 18c"
msgid_plural "Glock 18c"
msgstr[0] "格洛克18c"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Glock 18c is a compensated variant of the Glock 18. The compensation "
"allows for better control of recoil."
msgstr "格洛克18c是格洛克18的补偿器变体。补偿器能更好地控制后坐力。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "TEC-22"
msgid_plural "TEC-22"
msgstr[0] "TEC-22"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The more modern TEC-9 but fires the more easily found .22, still made using "
"stamped metal but now is also made with plastic! So its lighter."
msgstr "更现代的TEC-9，但发射更易找到的.22弹药，仍使用冲压金属制造，但现在也加入了塑料！所以更轻。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Bizon"
msgid_plural "Bizon"
msgstr[0] "野牛"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A Russian grade military SMG with a unique large capacity magazine. Used by "
"Russian special forces for CQB and tight environments. The Bizon is "
"accurate, and has excellent armour piercing capabilities."
msgstr "一款俄制军用冲锋枪，配有独特的大容量弹匣。俄罗斯特种部队用于CQB和狭窄环境。野牛精度高，并具有出色的穿甲能力。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Beretta Model 38"
msgid_plural "Beretta Model 38"
msgstr[0] "伯莱塔38型"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"Widely acknowledged as the best weapon to come out of Italy during WWII, its"
" simple design and ability to fire German 9mm ammo made it very easy to "
"produce."
msgstr "被广泛认为是二战期间意大利产的最佳武器，其简单设计及能发射德国9毫米弹药的能力使其易于生产。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Beretta Model 32/38"
msgid_plural "Beretta Model 32/38"
msgstr[0] "伯莱塔32/38型"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"Widely acknowledged as the best weapon to come out of Italy during WWII, its"
" simple design and ability to fire German 9mm ammo made it very easy to "
"produce. The 32/38 is the updated version of the 38."
msgstr "被公认为二战期间意大利生产的最佳武器，其简洁的设计和能够发射德国9毫米弹药的能力使其易于生产。32/38是38型的升级版本。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Scorpion Evo 3 S1"
msgid_plural "Scorpion Evo 3 S1"
msgstr[0] "蝎式Evo 3 S1"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The latest in line for the Scorpion sub-machine guns started by the Skorpion"
" vz 61, its large amount of rails and ability to be modified is one of the "
"reasons this is a good SMG, the other? It looks fucking cool that's why."
msgstr ""
"作为蝎式冲锋枪系列的最新成员，始于蝎式vz 61，其大量的导轨和可改装性是它成为一把优秀冲锋枪的原因之一，另一个原因？因为它看起来他妈的很酷。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Homemade SMG"
msgid_plural "Homemade SMG"
msgstr[0] "自制冲锋枪"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A homemade sub machine gun clearly made in someone's garage with clearly "
"some knowledge in gun designs. While not very accurate, and has high recoil."
" It fires a powerful round... 5.56"
msgstr ""
"一把显然是在某人车库里自制的冲锋枪，制作者显然具备一些枪械设计知识。虽然精度不高，后坐力也大，但它发射的是威力强大的弹药...5.56毫米。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "KP m/44"
msgid_plural "KP m/44"
msgstr[0] "KP m/44"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A Finish made clone of the very popular PPSh-43, while it does have some of "
"the same design, it still wasn't as good as the original."
msgstr "芬兰制造的广受欢迎的PPSh-43的仿制品，虽然设计上有些相似，但仍不及原版。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "AK-101"
msgid_plural "AK-101"
msgstr[0] "AK-101"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A AK designed to fire 5.56x45mm NATO. One of the many AK-blanks that are "
"coming out. Good accuracy though."
msgstr "一款设计用于发射5.56x45毫米北约弹药的AK步枪。这是众多新兴AK变种之一，不过精度不错。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "AK-102"
msgid_plural "AK-102"
msgstr[0] "AK-102"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"An AK designed to fire 5.56x45mm NATO. One of the many AK-blanks that are "
"coming out. Good accuracy though. Lighter and less volume than the AK-101"
msgstr "一款设计用于发射5.56x45毫米北约弹药的AK步枪。这是众多新兴AK变种之一，精度不错。比AK-101更轻，体积更小。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "AK-104"
msgid_plural "AK-104"
msgstr[0] "AK-104"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A plastic version of the beloved AKM, still performs the same though. The "
"AK-104 is the shortened version of the AK-103"
msgstr "备受喜爱的AKM的塑料版本，性能依旧相同。AK-104是AK-103的缩短版本。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgctxt "gun_type_type"
msgid "rifle"
msgstr "步枪"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "AKS-74"
msgid_plural "AKS-74"
msgstr[0] "AKS-74"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The paratrooper version of the AK-74, used by special Russian forces and "
"stalkers around the zone. Comes with a collapse-able stock"
msgstr "AK-74的空降兵版本，被俄罗斯特种部队和区域内的潜行者使用。配备可折叠枪托。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "AKS-74u"
msgid_plural "AKS-74u"
msgstr[0] "AKS-74u"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The even more paratrooper version of the AKS-74, used by special Russian "
"forces and stalkers around the zone. Comes with a collapse-able stock and "
"tons of recoil!"
msgstr "AKS-74的进一步空降兵版本，被俄罗斯特种部队和区域内的潜行者使用。配备可折叠枪托，后坐力巨大！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "AK-12"
msgid_plural "AK-12"
msgstr[0] "AK-12"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The newest AK in the line, just a baby compared to what all the other ones "
"have gone through. This one decides to embrace western culture and has the "
"ability to shoot 5.56 NATO"
msgstr "AK系列的最新成员，与其他前辈相比还是个婴儿。这款枪决定拥抱西方文化，能够发射5.56毫米北约弹药。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The newest AK in the line, just a baby compared to what all the other ones "
"have gone through. This one said fuck America and NATO and stuck with the "
"5.45x39"
msgstr "AK系列的最新成员，与其他前辈相比还是个婴儿。这款枪对美国佬和北约说不，坚持使用5.45x39毫米弹药。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "CZ 805 BREN"
msgid_plural "CZ 805 BREN"
msgstr[0] "CZ 805 BREN"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The replacement of the vz 58, the CZ 805 surpasses any qualification of a "
"good gun, it's an amazing gun. One of the best."
msgstr "作为vz 58的替代品，CZ 805超越了任何好枪的标准，它是一把出色的枪，属于顶级之列。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "EM-2 Janson"
msgid_plural "EM-2 Janson"
msgstr[0] "EM-2 詹森"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A experimental bullpup designed combat rifle. It was adopted by the UK in "
"1951, but very quickly was dropped, not because it was bad. But because the "
"UK was tying ties with NATO. This one shoots the powerful 30-06"
msgstr ""
"一款实验性的无托结构战斗步枪。英国于1951年采用，但很快就被放弃，并非因为它不好，而是因为英国正与北约建立联系。这款枪发射威力强大的.30-06弹药。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "MSBS Radon"
msgid_plural "MSBS Radon"
msgstr[0] "MSBS 氡"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The standard rifle used by the Poland Military in 2031, There are two "
"versions of this rifle. This one is the Normal version, which looks a lot "
"like the ACR and performs like it as well... Huh"
msgstr "波兰军队在2031年使用的标准步枪，这款步枪有两个版本。这是常规版本，看起来很像ACR，性能也相似...嗯。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The standard rifle used by the Poland Military in 2031, There are two "
"versions of this rifle. This one is the bullpup version, which is like a PDW"
" but a hell of a lot more scary."
msgstr "波兰军队在2031年使用的标准步枪，这款步枪有两个版本。这是无托版本，像是一把个人防卫武器，但威力要可怕得多。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "AAC Honey Badger"
msgid_plural "AAC Honey Badger"
msgstr[0] "AAC 蜜獾"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The AAC Honey Badger is the premier PDW in the modern world. Short, sleek, "
"and silent as hell. The AAC uses the .300 AC Blackout bullet to achieve sub-"
"sonic velocity and super-sonic velocity with just a change of the magazine."
msgstr ""
"AAC蜜獾是现代世界顶级的个人防卫武器。短小、流畅，且极其安静。AAC使用.300 AAC "
"Blackout弹药，仅通过更换弹匣就能实现亚音速和超音速的切换。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Grunt"
msgid_plural "Grunt"
msgstr[0] "咕噜兵"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A modified SCAR L made by some unknown soldier. It has been painted a leaf "
"camouflage and features a longer barrel then the base SCAR L, dog tags whose"
" name has long sense faded away are wrapped around the front end of the gun."
" And magazines jungle taped together clasp to the magazine well. But what "
"makes this weapon stand out is its two M203 Big boys. Two M203 launchers are"
" fashioned to the sides of the SCAR. With a activator switch for each one "
"taped to the magazine well. An amazing gun, unique to the Cataclysm."
msgstr ""
"一把由某位无名士兵改造的SCAR L步枪。它被涂上了树叶迷彩，枪管比基础版SCAR "
"L更长，前端缠绕着姓名早已模糊不清的狗牌。弹匣井上夹着用丛林胶带捆在一起的弹匣。但让这把武器脱颖而出的是它的两个M203“大块头”——两个M203榴弹发射器被安装在SCAR的两侧，每个的击发开关都用胶带固定在弹匣井旁。这是一把令人惊叹的枪，在《灾变》中独一无二。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Steyr Scout"
msgid_plural "Steyr Scouts"
msgstr[0] "斯泰尔侦察兵"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Steyr scout is a long range, compact siper rifle meant for scouting "
"teams. It fires the powerful 7.62x51mm round and packs one hell of a punch"
msgstr "斯泰尔侦察兵是一款为侦察小队设计的远程紧凑型狙击步枪。它发射威力强大的7.62x51毫米弹药，火力十足。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Accuracy International AX308"
msgid_plural "Accuracy International AX308s"
msgstr[0] "精密国际AX308"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Accuracy International AX308 is a state of the art sniper rifle used by "
"modern sniper teams from around the globe. It's amazing capabilities for "
"taking out enemies from afar is only offset by the fact that it's rare and "
"not many were made."
msgstr "精密国际AX308是一款现代狙击小队使用的尖端狙击步枪，全球各地均有配备。它出色的远程歼敌能力，唯一的缺点是数量稀少，产量有限。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Accuracy International L96A1"
msgid_plural "Accuracy International L96A1s"
msgstr[0] "精密国际L96A1"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The L96A1 is a British designed and manufactured sniper rifle that debuted "
"back in 1982. While an old rifle, the L96A1 still proves itself on the "
"battlefield compared to newer sniper rifles."
msgstr "L96A1是一款英国设计与制造的狙击步枪，最早于1982年亮相。虽然是一款老式步枪，但相比新型狙击步枪，L96A1在战场上依然表现出色。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "DSR-1"
msgid_plural "DSR-1s"
msgstr[0] "DSR-1"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The DSR-1 is an incredibly futuristic firearm. Toting the 7.62x51mm cartage,"
" it's power and accuracy is very commendable. But it's reliability and ease "
"of use is questionable... Seriously, where do you put the magazine?!"
msgstr ""
"DSR-1是一款极具未来感的枪械。使用7.62x51毫米弹药，其威力和精度值得称道。但它的可靠性和易用性令人怀疑……说真的，弹匣该插哪儿？！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Sako RK95-TP"
msgid_plural "Sako RK95-TP"
msgstr[0] "萨科RK95-TP"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A weapon used by the gods of war. A weapon that is used for both good and "
"evil. This gun was born in the fire forges of hell and blessed in the Garden"
" of Eden. This weapon has no commanders, or followers. The Sako has saved "
"many of survivors. It might just save you..."
msgstr ""
"战争之神使用的武器。一把亦正亦邪的枪。它诞生于地狱的熔炉，又在伊甸园中受祝福。这把武器没有统帅，也没有追随者。萨科拯救了许多幸存者。或许它也能救你……"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "PSG1"
msgid_plural "PSG1"
msgstr[0] "PSG1"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The PSG1 is Germany's premier sniper rifle. Accurate, Damaging, and super "
"cool looking, this weapon sure is a blast..."
msgstr "PSG1是德国的顶级狙击步枪。精准、威力强大、外观超酷，这把武器绝对够劲……"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M16"
msgid_plural "M16"
msgstr[0] "M16"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The first generation M16 used during Vietnam. If the history books tell you "
"this was a bad gun, they were a little wrong. It's accurate, low weight and "
"volume, while using a fairly easy to find caliber. Just clean it once in "
"awhile okay?"
msgstr ""
"越战时期使用的第一代M16。如果历史书告诉你这是把烂枪，那它们有点错了。它精准、轻便小巧，而且使用相当常见的口径。记得偶尔清理一下就行，好吗？"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M16A1"
msgid_plural "M16A1"
msgstr[0] "M16A1"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The second generation M16 after soldiers told their superiors that the "
"original felt like a toy. It features a longer barrel and lower rate of "
"fire, but much higher accuracy and reliability."
msgstr "第二代M16，在士兵向上级反映原版感觉像玩具后诞生。它采用更长的枪管和较低的射速，但精度和可靠性大幅提高。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M16A2"
msgid_plural "M16A2"
msgstr[0] "M16A2"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The third generation M16. Used during the Iraq war, it didn't prove very "
"well for the CQB that the marines had to face. Which is where the M4 stepped"
" in. But in the Cataclysm, you don't need to worry about terrorists with "
"AKs, only zombies with electricity powers..."
msgstr ""
"第三代M16。在伊拉克战争中使用，但面对海军陆战队遭遇的近距离战斗时表现不佳。这正是M4登场的地方。但在《灾变》中，你无需担心手持AK的恐怖分子，只需对付有电击能力的僵尸……"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M16A3"
msgid_plural "M16A3"
msgstr[0] "M16A3"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The fourth generation M16, which featured a lower rate of fire in favour of "
"making the M16 into a battle rifle. A good call, seeing that this is the "
"most accurate M16 at that time. A real brute stopper."
msgstr "第四代M16，通过降低射速将M16转变为战斗步枪。明智之举，因为这是当时最精准的M16。真正的猛兽终结者。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M16A4"
msgid_plural "M16A4"
msgstr[0] "M16A4"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The last generation M16, Now a true battle rifle. Rails up the wazoo, and "
"better at close quarters thanks to its tri-burst system. A reliable, "
"accurate, damaging combat rifle."
msgstr "最后一代M16，如今已是真正的战斗步枪。导轨遍布全身，得益于其三连发系统，在近距离作战中表现更佳。一把可靠、精准、威力强大的战斗步枪。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M110 SASS"
msgid_plural "M110 SASS"
msgstr[0] "M110 SASS"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A sniper rifle based on the M16A4, extremely accurate and damaging thanks to"
" the power 7.62x51mm round that it fires."
msgstr "一款基于M16A4的狙击步枪，得益于其发射的强力7.62x51毫米弹药，极其精准且威力强大。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M4 SOPMOD"
msgid_plural "M4 SOPMOD"
msgstr[0] "M4 SOPMOD"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The military issued M4A1; the SOPMOD, also called the Block 1, was a "
"advancement in M4A1 tech and allows for a more accurate, and reliable M4."
msgstr "军方配发的M4A1；SOPMOD，也称为Block 1，是M4A1技术的一次进步，提供了更精准、更可靠的M4。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M4 Block II"
msgid_plural "M4 Block II"
msgstr[0] "M4 Block II"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The special forces issued M4A1. The Block II was used by Navy Seals during "
"the beginning of the Cataclysm. And has lasted up to this point. Need I say "
"more?"
msgstr "特种部队配发的M4A1。Block II在《灾变》初期由海豹突击队使用，并一直留存至今。还需要我多说吗？"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "De Lisle Commando"
msgid_plural "De Lisle Commando"
msgstr[0] "德利尔突击队"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The De Lisle Commando is a short, carbine styled bolt action rifle using .45"
" caliber with an integrated suppressor. Arguably the most silent rifle ever "
"created, its ability as a survival tool is amazing."
msgstr "德利尔突击步枪是一款短小的卡宾风格栓动步枪，使用.45口径弹药并配有内置消音器。它堪称史上最安静的步枪，作为生存工具的能力令人惊叹。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "FG42"
msgid_plural "FG42s"
msgstr[0] "FG42"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"Germany's go-to paratrooper weapon during WWII, while not the most reliable,"
" it still caused many casualties on the allied side. A weapon ahead of its "
"time, this one is a modern reproduction chambered in .30-06."
msgstr "这是二战期间德国伞兵的首选武器，虽然可靠性并非最佳，但仍给盟军造成大量伤亡。这款超前于时代的武器是现代复刻版，使用.30-06口径弹药。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "FX-05 Xiuhcoatl"
msgid_plural "FX-05 Xiuhcoatl"
msgstr[0] "FX-05 火蛇"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Mexican FX-05 Xiuhcoatl is translated into 'Fire Snake' which is awesome"
" in it of itself, but what is most important is it's rifling design, instead"
" of grooves, it has ridges. Making it unique and accurate."
msgstr "墨西哥FX-05火蛇步枪的名字意为'火焰之蛇'，本身就很酷炫，但最重要的是它的膛线设计——不是凹槽而是凸脊。这使其独具特色且精度出众。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "H&K G36c"
msgid_plural "H&K G36c"
msgstr[0] "H&K G36c"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A smaller version of the G36, the G36c is made for CQB. Light, accurate, and"
" very reliable, its the ultimate weapon for any special ops soldier"
msgstr "作为G36的紧凑版本，G36c专为近距离作战设计。它轻巧、精准且极其可靠，是特种部队士兵的终极武器。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "FAMAS"
msgid_plural "FAMAS"
msgstr[0] "FAMAS"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A bullpup assault rifle made with accuracy in mind. The weapon is very "
"modular, even having the ability to put wing mirrors on the sides... Why?"
msgstr "这款无托突击步枪以精度为核心设计。武器模块化程度极高，甚至能在两侧安装后视镜……为什么？"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "AA-12"
msgid_plural "AA-12"
msgstr[0] "AA-12"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The US made automatic shotgun features a fully automatic recoil reducer "
"system that provides excess death dealing when in close quarters. "
msgstr "这款美国制造的自动霰弹枪配备全自动后坐力抑制系统，在近距离交战时能提供超强的致命打击能力。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "USAS 12"
msgid_plural "USAS 12s"
msgstr[0] "USAS 12"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Franchi Spas 15"
msgid_plural "Franchi Spas 15"
msgstr[0] "弗兰基Spas 15"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Italian made Spas 15 was a update on the great Spas 12, making much "
"needed improvements on loading of shells and rate of fire. It's got a box "
"magazine and can go full auto!"
msgstr "意大利制造的Spas 15是经典Spas 12的升级版，在装弹速度和射速方面做了必要改进。它采用弹匣供弹并能全自动射击！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Mossberg 590A1"
msgid_plural "Mossberg 590A1"
msgstr[0] "莫斯伯格590A1"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Mossberg 590A1 is a modern military pump action shotgun used by special "
"forces soldiers around the globe. Known for its brutality on the field. The "
"weapon is by far a most dangerous firearm."
msgstr "莫斯伯格590A1是现代军用泵动霰弹枪，被全球特种部队使用。以其战场上的凶悍著称，是目前最危险的枪械之一。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Open Action Revolver"
msgid_plural "Open Action Revolver"
msgstr[0] "开膛式转轮手枪"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"This weapon seems to be a mix of a Semi-Automatic Pistol and a Revolver. "
"Very peculiar weapon but seems to be in working condition. Accurate, "
"powerful, and fecking awesome looking."
msgstr "这把武器似乎是半自动手枪与转轮手枪的混合体。非常奇特但似乎处于可用状态。精准、威力强大，而且外观酷炫到爆。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Colt Single Action Army"
msgid_plural "Colt Single Action Army"
msgstr[0] "柯尔特单动陆军"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "A Russian once said this was the best gun in the world. Nuff said"
msgstr "曾有俄罗斯人称这是世界上最好的枪。无需多言。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Colt Python"
msgid_plural "Colt Python"
msgstr[0] "柯尔特蟒蛇"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"Weapon of choice for many action heroes and zombie survivalists, this pistol"
" has proven many times that it is one of the best"
msgstr "作为众多动作英雄和僵尸生存者的首选武器，这款手枪多次证明了它是最佳之一。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Ruger Blackhawk"
msgid_plural "Ruger Blackhawk"
msgstr[0] "鲁格黑鹰"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"One of the most versatile revolvers to date, this break-action revolver "
"features some of the best accuracy of any revolver"
msgstr "这是迄今为止最多功能的转轮手枪之一，这款折开式转轮手枪拥有同类武器中最佳的精度。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Colt Detective Special"
msgid_plural "Colt Detective Special"
msgstr[0] "柯尔特侦探特装型"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The gun that started the Snub-nose revolution. Features small compatibility "
"and the ability to blow someone face off."
msgstr "这把枪开启了短管转轮手枪的革命。具有小巧的兼容性和轰飞人脸的能力。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Winchester Model 1873"
msgid_plural "Winchester Model 1873"
msgstr[0] "温彻斯特1873型"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A .44-40 caliber repeating rifle straight out of wild west films. This one "
"has some age to it but like a old mule, it kicks pretty damn hard. Looks "
"like someone had retooled the gun for .44, guess the 44-40 was too "
"expensive."
msgstr ""
"这把.44-40口径连发步枪直接出自西部电影。虽有些年头，但像老骡子一样后坐力惊人。看来有人将它改造成了.44口径，估计是44-40弹药太贵了。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Remington Model 7600"
msgid_plural "Remington Model 7600"
msgstr[0] "雷明顿7600型"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Remington Model 7600 is a pump-action hunting rifle that shoots "
"7.62x51mm. Proves to be pretty effective against zombie brains."
msgstr "雷明顿7600型是发射7.62x51mm弹药的泵动式狩猎步枪。事实证明它对僵尸脑袋相当有效。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Dragunov SVD"
msgid_plural "Dragunov SVDs"
msgstr[0] "德拉古诺夫 SVD"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Dragunov SVD is a semi-automatic sniper rifle in service from 1954 to "
"modern times via the Russian military and friends. Gas operated and "
"incredibly reliable; the SVD is sure to bring out the sniper stalker in you!"
msgstr ""
"德拉古诺夫 SVD 是一款半自动狙击步枪，自 1954 年起在俄罗斯军队及其盟友中服役至今。采用导气式设计，可靠性极高；SVD "
"定能激发你内心的狙击潜行者！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Ots-03 SVU"
msgid_plural "Ots-03 SVU"
msgstr[0] "Ots-03 SVU"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A Russian bullpup sniper rifle which is a conversion for the SVD Dragunov. "
"The length of a pdw with the range and power of a SVD you can surely breach "
"and clear any room now!"
msgstr "一款俄罗斯无托式狙击步枪，由 SVD 德拉古诺夫改装而来。拥有 PDW 的长度与 SVD 的射程和威力，你现在肯定能突入并清空任何房间！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Obrez"
msgid_plural "Obrez"
msgstr[0] "奥布雷兹"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"An Mosin Nagant that is shortened so much that it looks like a pistol. And "
"is a pistol; that shoots 7.62x54R..."
msgstr "一支被截短到看起来像手枪的莫辛-纳甘步枪。而且它确实是一把手枪；发射 7.62x54R 子弹……"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Ithaca M37"
msgid_plural "Ithaca M37"
msgstr[0] "伊萨卡 M37"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Ithaca M37 is a extremely popular shotgun for home defense and cool "
"looks. This one has been modified by cutting the stock off."
msgstr "伊萨卡 M37 是一款极受欢迎的家防霰弹枪，外观酷炫。这支经过改装，枪托已被锯掉。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Striker"
msgid_plural "Striker"
msgstr[0] "打击者"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The South African Striker provides large capacity to the shot-gunner's world"
" with its revolving wheel of death. Being semi-auto, its very fast in "
"unloading it's payload. But don't expect perfect delivery every time."
msgstr "南非的打击者以其致命的旋转弹轮为霰弹枪世界提供了大容量。作为半自动武器，它能极快地倾泻弹药。但别指望每次都能完美投送。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Bren Light Machine Gun"
msgid_plural "Bren Light Machine Gun"
msgstr[0] "布伦轻机枪"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Bren Light Machine gun is a fixed bypod, top loaded machine gun that "
"more or less acts like a anti-personnel SAW. Deadly when used properly - "
"this one has been chambered in 7.62x51mm NATO. Must be a post-war model."
msgstr ""
"布伦轻机枪是一款固定两脚架、顶部供弹的机枪，或多或少扮演着反人员 SAW 的角色。使用得当时威力致命——这支已改为 7.62x51mm NATO "
"口径。想必是战后型号。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "DP Light Machine Gun"
msgid_plural "DP Light Machine Gun"
msgstr[0] "DP 轻机枪"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The DP is a WWII squad automatic weapon that has one hell of a round coming "
"out of the barrel. Very powerful, and with high capacity."
msgstr "DP 是一款二战班用自动武器，从枪管射出的子弹威力惊人。非常强大，且容量高。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "FN Minimi"
msgid_plural "FN Minimi"
msgstr[0] "FN 米尼米"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A paratrooper version of the ever so popular M249 SAW, it features a "
"skeletal stock and light weight. Along with all those SAW parts."
msgstr "广受欢迎的 M249 SAW 的伞兵版本，采用骨架枪托，重量轻。并保留了所有 SAW 部件。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Lewis Gun"
msgid_plural "Lewis Gun"
msgstr[0] "刘易斯机枪"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Lewis gun is a water cooled machine gun that is meant to be used in a "
"prone position, but thanks to game reasons, you can't prone down to use the "
"thing properly. But if you can use it, it's one hell of a machine gun."
msgstr "刘易斯机枪是一款水冷机枪，本应在卧姿下使用，但由于游戏原因，你无法趴下正确使用它。但如果你能用上，它绝对是款厉害的机枪。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "RPK"
msgid_plural "RPK"
msgstr[0] "RPK"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The RPK is the light machine gun varient in the AK family. Using the "
"7.62x39mm round means that there is going to be a lot of lead spewing out of"
" the barrel when this baby is lit up."
msgstr "RPK 是 AK 家族中的轻机枪变体。使用 7.62x39mm 子弹意味着当这小家伙开火时，枪管会喷涌出大量铅弹。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "PKM"
msgid_plural "PKM"
msgstr[0] "PKM"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The PKM is the Heavy machine gun in the AK family. And unlike everything "
"else, it's internals are the only thing that is based on the AK. The look "
"and feel is it's own thing."
msgstr "PKM 是 AK 家族中的重机枪。与其他成员不同，只有其内部结构基于 AK。外观和手感自成一体。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "MG3"
msgid_plural "MG3"
msgstr[0] "MG3"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The MG3 is the modernized version of the MG42. It features more lightweight "
"parts and a slimmer magazine. It's fire rate is still the same 1,200 rounds "
"a minute. So be ready to reload this baby a LOT."
msgstr "MG3 是 MG42 的现代化版本。采用更轻的部件和更窄的弹匣。射速仍为每分钟 1,200 发。所以准备好频繁为这小家伙装弹吧。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "The Hacksaw"
msgid_plural "The Hacksaw"
msgstr[0] "钢锯"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"A heavily modified MG3, clearly made in someone's basement. It seems ready "
"for anything. The word Hacksaw is scratched into the right side. Under the "
"word Bundeswehr so faint you can barely see it. A rag is wrapped around the "
"heat shield so the user can hold it by it. But the stock seems the most "
"unique of all the modifications. It seems to float, only held by some para "
"cord and a spring. And when you push your shoulder into the firing position."
" It seems to push against you. Considerably reducing recoil."
msgstr ""
"一支重度改装的 "
"MG3，显然是在某人的地下室里制造的。它似乎已为一切做好准备。“钢锯”一词刻在右侧。“联邦国防军”字样下方，模糊得几乎看不见。隔热罩上缠着破布，以便使用者握持。但枪托似乎是所有改装中最独特的。它似乎悬浮着，仅由伞绳和弹簧固定。当你抵肩进入射击姿势时，它似乎会反向推挤，显著减少后坐力。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "RPD"
msgid_plural "RPD"
msgstr[0] "RPD"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The RPD is the light machine gun varient in the AK family. Using the "
"7.62x39mm round means that there is going to be a lot of lead spewing out of"
" the barrel when this baby is lit up."
msgstr "RPD 是 AK 家族中的轻机枪变体。使用 7.62x39mm 子弹意味着当这小家伙开火时，枪管会喷涌出大量铅弹。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "SMLE Number 4"
msgid_plural "SMLE Number 4"
msgstr[0] "SMLE 4 号"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The Short, Magazine Lee-Enfield Number Four - The quintessential British "
"service rifle, along with other members of the Lee-Enfield family. Rule "
"Britannia!"
msgstr "短弹匣李-恩菲尔德 4 号步枪——典型的英军制式步枪，与李-恩菲尔德家族的其他成员一样。不列颠统治！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Gewehr 98"
msgid_plural "G98"
msgstr[0] "Gewehr 98"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"Developed in 1898, this gun would later become the basis for many rifles the"
" world over, from the Springfield to the Type 24 to the K98k. Today, its "
"action is primarily used in hunting rifles."
msgstr "这款枪于1898年研发，后来成为全球众多步枪的基础，从春田步枪到二四式步枪再到K98k。如今，其枪机结构主要用于猎枪。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Type 24"
msgid_plural "T24"
msgstr[0] "二四式步枪"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"Developed with German support in China, this would become one of the most "
"domestically produced rifles in Chinese service in WWII. A smaller, more "
"accurate version of the G98, it was well-liked."
msgstr "这款步枪在中国由德国支持研发，成为二战期间中国军队中产量最高的国产步枪之一。作为G98的更小巧、更精准版本，它备受青睐。"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Mosin-Nagant 28/30"
msgid_plural "Finnish Mosin"
msgstr[0] "莫辛-纳甘M28/30"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"Based on the famous 91/30, this Finnish Mosin represents one of the "
"pinnacles of the bolt-action system. As it was a Civil Guard model before "
"the Winter War, the rifle was greatly improved with a focus on accuracy. "
"Perkele!"
msgstr ""
"基于著名的91/30步枪，这款芬兰版莫辛代表了栓动系统的巅峰之一。作为冬季战争前的国民卫队型号，该步枪经过大幅改进，重点提升了精度。Perkele！"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "M17 Enfield"
msgid_plural "M17 Enfield"
msgstr[0] "M17恩菲尔德"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"Despite being less famous than its cousin, the Springfield 1903, the Enfield"
" 1917 saw large amounts of service with American soldiers in WWI and "
"internationally into WWII. Rule... Britannia?"
msgstr "尽管不如其表亲春田1903步枪出名，恩菲尔德1917步枪在一战中被美军大量使用，并延续至二战期间的国际战场。统治吧……不列颠尼亚？"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid "Needlefire Rifle"
msgid_plural "Needlefire Rifles"
msgstr[0] "针发枪"

#: .\art_weapons.json
msgid ""
"The pinnacle of black-powder firearm development, the needlefire system uses"
" a protruding needle style of firing pin, allowing it to use breech-loading "
"paper cartridges, allowing for relatively rapid and precise fire. This in "
"particular seems to be a reproduction of a Chassepot, which was the most "
"highly developed of its kind - capable of out-ranging its competitors nearly"
" 2-1. "
msgstr ""
"作为黑火药火器发展的巅峰，针发系统采用突出的针状击针，使其能够使用后膛装填的纸壳弹，实现相对快速而精准的射击。这尤其像夏塞波步枪的复制品，是该类火器中最高度发展的型号——射程几乎是对手的两倍。"

#: .\modinfo.json
msgid "Artyoms' Gun Emporium - Reloaded"
msgstr "阿尔乔姆的枪械商场 - 重装上阵"

#. ~ Description for Artyoms' Gun Emporium - Reloaded
#: .\modinfo.json
msgid "Adds all the guns that YOU need to survive the Cataclysm"
msgstr "添加所有你在灾变中生存所需的枪支"
